article.description: Kahlil Small had a career-high 20 points, and Carrington Love scored 11 of his 15 in the second half to help Green Bay rally for a 76-68 win over Wright State on Monday night.
article.headline: Small, Love help Green Bay beat Wright State 76-68
article.linkText: Small, Love help Green Bay beat Wright State 76-68
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wisc. -- Kahlil Small had a career-high 20 points, and Carrington Love scored 11 of his 15 in the second half to help Green Bay rally for a 76-68 win over Wright State on Monday night. Jordan Fouse had 11 points while Charles Cooper scored 10 for Green Bay (9-5, 2-0 Horizon League). Wright State (7-8, 1-1) shot 53 percent from the field in the first half and took a 45-35 lead into the break. Green Bay scored the first seven points of the second half before using a 13-4 run to take a 55-54 lead -- its first since midway through the first half -- on a 3-pointer by Love with 11:39 to play. After JT Yoho's layup on the other end, Tevin Findlay hit a 3 to put the Phoenix in front for good. Green Bay made 12 of 16 free throws in the final 7:17. Yoho finished with 17 points and a career-high 13 rebounds.
